      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It's normal to feel drained after an intense experience, and the weight of perceived meaning can add to the exhaustion. In some cases, the best approach is to let go of the need to find value and simply end the chapter. It's okay to acknowledge that this journey has come to a close and give yourself permission to rest and recharge.",
      "source": "target",
